Class OperationBuilder

java.lang.Object
pt.up.fe.els2024.builders.Builder
pt.up.fe.els2024.builders.OperationBuilder
public class OperationBuilder extends Builder
A builder class for performing operations on tables and columns. Allows adding, renaming, and removing columns, as well as performing mathematical operations between numeric columns. Designed for use with TableBuilder to build and modify tables.

    • sum

      public OperationBuilder sum()
      Computes the sum of numeric values in each column of the result table and appends the total as a new row. - For columns containing numeric values (`Number`), it calculates the sum of all rows excluding the added rows. - For columns containing strings that can be converted to numbers, it attempts the conversion and calculates the sum. - For non-numeric columns or invalid strings, appends "N/A" to the column.
      Returns:
      the current OperationBuilder instance for method chaining.

    • average

      public OperationBuilder average()
      Calculates the average of numeric values in each column of the result table and appends it as a new row. - For columns containing numeric values (`Number`), it calculates the average of all rows excluding the added rows. - For columns containing strings that can be converted to numbers, it attempts the conversion and calculates the average. - For non-numeric columns or invalid strings, appends "N/A" to the column. The calculated average for numeric columns is rounded to two decimal places.
      Returns:
      the current OperationBuilder instance for method chaining.
